# PLUS Design System - Agent Rules

## Figma links (mandatory)

**When the user provides a Figma link**, use Figma MCP **before** building or prototyping from that design:

1. **Get design context** — Extract specs/layout/code for the selected frame or node.
2. **Get screenshot** — Capture the design so layout and visuals can be matched.

Do not skip these steps. If Figma MCP is unavailable, say so and ask for a screenshot or export instead.

## IMPORTANT: Skills-Based Framework

This project uses a skills-based agent framework. 

**Read the main agent file first:**

→ `.agent/AGENT.md`

## Quick Reference

| Skill | Location | When to Use |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| learn-plus | `.agent/skills/learn-plus/SKILL.md` | Questions, onboarding |
| design-consulting | `.agent/skills/design-consulting/SKILL.md` | Planning, brainstorming |
| prototyping | `playground/prototyping/README.md` | Prototypes — modes & baseline; implementation uses building skill |
| building | `.agent/skills/building/SKILL.md` | New patterns from Figma |
| maintaining | `.agent/skills/maintaining/SKILL.md` | Update existing code |

## Foundations

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.agent/foundations/tech-stack.md` | Versions, commands |
| `.agent/foundations/tokens.md` | Design tokens |
